{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_8z7iajdgUDge6hhAxPE8s86t","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# LMThing — Core Runtime Developer Guide (`sdk/org`)\n2\t\n3\tThe agent runtime and everything built directly on it: `@lmthing/core` (QuickJS WASM sandbox, streaming\n4\tstatement pipeline, yield protocol, spaces/forks/delegates/tasklists, typecheck, budgets), `@lmthing/cli`\n5\t(the `lmthing` binary + pod server), the shared libs, and the unified web SPA (`apps/web`).\n6\t\n7\tThe model does not call tools — **the model writes TypeScript**, one statement at a time, and the host\n8\tevaluates each statement as it streams in. A value-yielding call suspends the VM, aborts the stream, is\n9\tresolved host-side, and the results come back as a `VARIABLES` block on the next turn.\n10\t\n11\t## Source of truth — read this first\n12\t\n13\t> **[`org/docs/`](../../org/docs/README.md) (published at lmthing.org) is the single source of truth for\n14\t> this codebase.** Every factual sentence there carries a citation to the code that makes it true — a\n15\t> symbol anchor (`path#Symbol`) by preference, a line anchor (`path:Lstart-Lend`) where a symbol isn't\n16\t> appropriate. `pnpm docs:check` resolves them all as a hard CI gate. When this file disagrees with\n17\t> `org/docs`, `org/docs` wins. When `org/docs` disagrees with the **code**, the code wins and `org/docs`\n18\t> is fixed.\n19\t>\n20\t> **A change to code is not done until the matching `org/docs` page is updated in the same change.**\n21\t> The rule, the grounding convention, and the \"which doc moves with my change?\" table →\n22\t> [`org/docs/SYNC.md`](../../org/docs/SYNC.md).\n23\t\n24\tThis file is an **orientation index**: what lives here, how to run it, and where the real answer is.\n25\tKnowledge does not live here.\n26\t\n27\t## Workspace\n28\t\n29\t```bash\n30\tcd sdk/org\n31\tpnpm install                       # from lockfile\n32\tpnpm build                         # turbo run build → dist/\n33\tpnpm typecheck                     # tsc --noEmit across all packages (strict)\n34\tpnpm test                          # vitest run (co-located tests) — run from sdk/org, NOT the repo root\n35\tpnpm test libs/core/src/tasklist   # one directory / substring filter\n36\tpnpm dev                           # turbo run dev --parallel (watch + rebuild)\n37\tpnpm thing                         # CLI + web app on ONE port, both hot-reloading (scripts/thing-dev.mjs)\n38\t```\n39\t\n40\tRunning the CLI: `node libs/cli/dist/cli/bin.js --space <dir> \"<message>\"`. Keyless testing:\n41\t`--mock <file>` / `LM_MOCK=<file>` (scripted `streamFn`). `--repl` interactive · `--claude`\n42\tprogrammatic · `--web <port>` DevTools UI · `--request \"<msg>\"` headless single-shot · `--trace <file>`\n43\tNDJSON trace.\n44\t\n45\t- Every flag, subcommand and env var (model aliases, providers) → [`org/docs/cli-api/commands.md`](../../org/docs/cli-api/commands.md)\n46\t- Test runners, the two-workspace trap, the mock harness, live scenarios → [`org/docs/contributing/testing.md`](../../org/docs/contributing/testing.md)\n47\t- Debugging the eval/yield pipeline → [`org/docs/contributing/debugging.md`](../../org/docs/contributing/debugging.md)\n48\t\n49\t`.env` is read from `process.cwd()` only (`libs/cli/src/cli/bin.ts:L18`). In Claude Code web sessions\n50\tkeys are decrypted from `.env.encrypted` by `.claude/hooks/session-start.sh` — **if `TAVILY_API_KEY` or\n51\tanother secret is missing, ask for `ENV_DECRYPT_KEY` before proceeding.**\n52\t\n53\t## Layout\n54\t\n55\t`libs/{core,cli,ui,css,state,auth,utils,config}` · `libs/core/system-spaces/*` (the\n56\tshipped system + user spaces) · `apps/web` (the unified SPA — `/chat`, `/studio`, `/computer` as\n57\tclient-side routes) · `scenarios/` (live prod scenario runner).\n58\t\n59\t`@lmthing/core` never imports from `cli` or `ui` — it emits events and accepts a `RenderHost`.\n60\t\n61\tPackage-by-package detail → [`org/docs/libs/README.md`](../../org/docs/libs/README.md) · the surfaces →\n62\t[`chat/`](../../org/docs/chat/README.md) · [`studio/`](../../org/docs/studio/README.md) ·\n63\t[`computer/`](../../org/docs/computer/README.md).\n64\t\n65\t## Gotchas that bite while editing this code\n66\t\n67\tEach is one line; the grounded explanation is behind the link.\n68\t\n69\t- **Variables do not persist between evals** — each statement is its own module; the loop appends\n70\t  `globalThis['x'] = x` for every bound name. → [runtime/turn-loop](../../org/docs/runtime/turn-loop.md)\n71\t- **Yield-result binding is host-side**, not the QuickJS post-`await` continuation — it maps results onto\n72\t  the binding pattern but prefers `vm.getVar(name)` where they diverge (which is what recovers a yield\n73\t  nested inside another async function). → [runtime/turn-loop](../../org/docs/runtime/turn-loop.md)\n74\t- **A bridged host promise is disposed on settle, never on creation** — `resolve()`/`reject()` are no-ops\n75\t  after `dispose()`, so eager disposal permanently neuters a nested `await`. And **`vm.dispose()` must\n76\t  never throw**: it swallows QuickJS's `list_empty(&rt->gc_obj_list)` abort, which is catchable and\n77\t  benign — propagating it turns an already-produced fork result into a spurious rejection. `LM_QJS_DEBUG=1`\n78\t  loads the assertion-tracking debug WASM when hunting a real handle leak. → [runtime/](../../org/docs/runtime/README.md)\n79\t- **Not granted ⇒ not injected AND absent from the DTS** — one `CapabilityProfile` drives both, so a call\n80\t  the context cannot make fails typecheck (retryable) instead of throwing. This is why `ask`/`fork`/\n81\t  `tasklist` in a fork or delegate is a *typecheck* error. → [runtime/typecheck](../../org/docs/runtime/typecheck.md)\n82\t- **Never forbid a tool in prose — disable it in tasklist frontmatter** (`role`, `functions: [...]`,\n83\t  `canDelegateTo`); the host enforces it, prose does not.\n84\t  → [runtime/fork-and-tasklists](../../org/docs/runtime/fork-and-tasklists.md) · [format/space/tasklists](../../org/docs/format/space/tasklists/README.md)\n85\t- **There is NO generic filesystem on the model surface** — `readFile`/`writeFile`/`editFile`/`listDir`/\n86\t  `glob`/`grep` and raw `execShell`/`readFileRaw`/`writeFileRaw` are absent from every agent's DTS.\n87\t  Persistence goes ONLY through typed, root-scoped writers (`writeProject*`, the architect builder\n88\t  functions); reads through `listProjectDir`/`readProjectFile` (project) or `listSpaceDir`/`readSpaceFile`\n89\t  (space). The ONE exception is the **engineer**, which holds `fs:scratch`: it keeps the generic fs/shell\n90\t  jailed to a `.lmthing/scratch/<random>` dir it must `createScratch()` first, and RETURNS code for its\n91\t  caller to persist. `readFileRaw`/`writeFileRaw` survive only as internal host primitives (memory/todos +\n92\t  architect builder bodies, which aren't typechecked against the model DTS).\n93\t  → [runtime-globals/](../../org/docs/runtime-globals/README.md)\n94\t- **Adding a worker-run seam ⇒ add its tsup entry.** Store code (space emitters, space hook handlers, code\n95\t  nodes) resolves its worker entry as a sibling of the bundled module; a missing `worker-load-entry` in\n96\t  `libs/cli/tsup.config.ts` ships an image where every emitter scan and space-hook dispatch fails in prod\n97\t  (unit tests run from `src/` and miss it). → [`libs/cli/tsup.config.ts`](./libs/cli/tsup.config.ts)\n98\t- **System spaces auto-adopt source/image updates** — a pristine materialized copy re-syncs on boot;\n99\t  locally-edited ones hold back (adopt with `--adopt-system-spaces`). → [`libs/cli/src/cli/runtime-init.ts`](./libs/cli/src/cli/runtime-init.ts) · [system-spaces/](../../org/docs/system-spaces/README.md)\n100\t- **`pnpm --filter @lmthing/core test` is a silent no-op** — core has no `test` script. Use\n101\t  `cd sdk/org && pnpm test <path>`. → [contributing/testing](../../org/docs/contributing/testing.md)\n102\t\n103\t## Rules\n104\t\n105\t- **Always test every fix.** No fix is done until a test would have caught it.\n106\t- **Update the doc in the same change.** See [`org/docs/SYNC.md`](../../org/docs/SYNC.md). If you catch\n107\t  yourself explaining behaviour *here*, it belongs in `org/docs` — put it there and link it.\n108\t- **Issue lifecycle.** File a `.issues/` entry when a bug is found; delete it when fixed and tested.\n109\t  No issue file = no known bugs. (`.issues/` is the live list — do not mirror it here.)\n110\t- **Design system is mandatory.** Any web styling uses `@lmthing/css` tokens — never a raw color. Change\n111\t  colors only via `libs/css/src/tokens/tokens.json` + `pnpm --filter @lmthing/css generate` (never\n112\t  hand-edit `theme.css`). Enforced by `lint:tokens` (hard CI gate). → [design-system/](../../org/docs/design-system/README.md)\n113\t\n114\t## Task Index\n115\t\n116\tSource of truth is the `org/docs` page. Skills (`@.claude/skills/*`) are local *procedures* only.\n117\t\n118\t| Working on… | Read |\n119\t|---|---|\n120\t| the turn loop / yield protocol / budgets / retries / prose-drop | [org/docs/runtime/turn-loop.md](../../org/docs/runtime/turn-loop.md) |\n121\t| typecheck / the DTS overlay / transpile / the JSX runtime | [org/docs/runtime/typecheck.md](../../org/docs/runtime/typecheck.md) |\n122\t| forks + tasklist orchestration / roles / `forEach` / salvage / code nodes | [org/docs/runtime/fork-and-tasklists.md](../../org/docs/runtime/fork-and-tasklists.md) |\n123\t| `delegate()` / the registry / `canDelegateTo` / actions / auto-capture | [org/docs/runtime/delegation.md](../../org/docs/runtime/delegation.md) |\n124\t| space loading / system-space merge rules / project functions | [org/docs/runtime/spaces-loading.md](../../org/docs/runtime/spaces-loading.md) |\n125\t| the `Session` API / snapshots + resume / history summarization / tracing | [org/docs/runtime/sessions.md](../../org/docs/runtime/sessions.md) |\n126\t| a runtime global, or the 