{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_NeBZejQ25YPVl3KnuVVN81Rl","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: build_app\n3\toutput:\n4\t  ok: boolean\n5\t  detail: string\n6\tdependsOn: [build_specialist]\n7\tgoal: true\n8\trole: general\n9\tfunctions: []\n10\tcanDelegateTo:\n11\t  - system-appbuilder/automator\n12\t---\n13\t\n14\tBuild the live-project app after every inventoried specialist has finished. `request`,\n15\t`sourceSummary`, `attachmentIds`, `specialistFacts`, and `build_specialist` are in scope. Delegate to\n16\tthe live-project automator, which writes into this project's database and pages. Pass every attachment\n17\tid so it can read all supplied source files; include `specialistFacts` because image and audio facts\n18\tcannot be re-read. Mention any failed specialist build in the request, but still build from the\n19\tcomplete supplied source. The deliverable is not complete until it has source-derived rows and an\n20\topenable page backed by the project's own API; do not report a survey or data model as a finished\n21\tapp. Emit exactly one self-contained statement that delegates and resolves without relying on a later\n22\tstatement or cross-turn variable:\n23\t\n24\tcurrentTask.resolve(await delegate('system-appbuilder', 'automator', { query: String(request) + '\\n\\nBuild the complete live-project app now: write source-derived tables and rows, then write the project API and openable pages that show those rows.\\n\\nSource summary:\\n' + String(sourceSummary) + '\\n\\nFacts available only from image/audio analysis:\\n' + String(specialistFacts) + '\\n\\nSpecialist build results:\\n' + JSON.stringify(build_specialist), attachmentIds: attachmentIds as string[] }).then((app) => ({ ok: !!(app && app.ok === true), detail: JSON.stringify((app && app.data) ? app.data : {}) })));"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_fzpUJSbHB3H8gLDKEI4xloQi","session_id":"838823e9-9562-4e94-a4a8-ddea09a60dee","uuid":"484bab4b-55de-4da6-b09f-4