{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_8lxffShwuMS98UMbr7ZOk92M","type":"tool_result","content":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_app/06-build_hook.md:27:trigger back into `app-architect#build_app`). Emit ONE of these shapes for your `item`:\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/agents/app-architect/instruct.md:14:defaultAction: build_app\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/agents/app-architect/instruct.md:16:  - id: build_app\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/agents/app-architect/instruct.md:19:    tasklist: build_app\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/agents/app-architect/instruct.md:29:program: run the `build_app` tasklist and let the HOST drive the file-by-file build (design →\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/agents/app-architect/instruct.md:38:const t = await tasklist('build_app', { request: query });\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/agents/app-architect/instruct.md:54:  `build_app` tasklist, which already runs every step under your own authoring capabilities.\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/tasklists/organize_material/03-build_app.md:2:id: build_app\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:176:is no tool for it. Do NOT run `build_specialist`/`build_app` to \"make a project\" (that\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:210:Only path 4b (`build_app`) targets the store catalog — a NEW, separately-installable app template.\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:565:   const app = await delegate('system-appbuilder', 'app-architect', 'build_app', { query: '<the user request, verbatim>' });\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/knowledge/app_building/model/capability-model.md:55:builder cannot write a table; a data modeler cannot write a page. The build_app tasklist runs its\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/agents/automator/instruct.md:739:  \"export default { type: 'cron', every: '1d', trigger: 'system-appbuilder/app-architect#build_app' };\",\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/system-spaces-dag.test.ts:124:    expect(organize['build_app']!.canDelegateTo).toEqual(['system-appbuilder/automator']);\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/system-spaces-dag.test.ts:125:    expect(organize['build_app']!.instruction).toContain('live-project automator');\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/system-spaces-dag.test.ts:126:    expect(organize['build_app']!.instruction).toContain('source-derived rows and an\\nopenable page backed by the project\\'s own API');\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/system-spaces-dag.test.ts:127:    expect(organize['build_app']!.instruction).toContain('exactly one self-contained statement');\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/system-spaces-dag.test.ts:128:    expect(resolveGoalTask(organize)!.id).toBe('build_app');\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/system-spaces-dag.test.ts:160:  it('appbuilder build_app fans out per-file with valid roles and a finalize goal', async () => {\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/system-spaces-dag.test.ts:162:    const tasks = await loadTasklistFromSpace(space, 'build_app');\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/system-spaces-dag.test.ts:176:    expect(space.tasklists['build_app']!.input).toEqual({ request: 'string' });\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/README.md:66:**Authoring plane — [format/](./format/README.md).** A *space* is a portable bundle of agents plus their deterministic `functions/`, `knowledge/`, `tasklists/`, UI `components/` and `events/` emitter defs, loaded by `loadSpace` (`sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/load.ts`). A *project* is an application: a project-rooted SQLite DB from `database/*.json`, worker-isolated Node handlers in `api/`, client-side React `pages/`, in-proc `hooks/`, and its own project-scoped `spaces/` (`sdk/org/libs/cli/src/app/loader.ts` `loadProjectApp`). Ten system spaces ship with the runtime and are materialized into `<root>/system/spaces/` — `system-global`, `system-engineer`, `system-architect`, `system-research`, `system-appbuilder`, `system-vision`, `system-files`, `system-store`, `user-memory`, `user-thing` (`sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/system.ts#SYSTEM_SPACE_NAMES`).\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/system-spaces/README.md:44:| **`system-appbuilder`** | `app-architect` | `build_app` *(default)* | Builds a whole application — **the store-catalog template path**. Runs the `build_app` tasklist and reports; may delegate one slice to a specialist (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/agents/app-architect/instruct.md:L29-L54`). |\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/system-spaces/README.md:93:  THING --> AA[\"system-appbuilder/app-architect<br/>build_app\"]\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/system-spaces/README.md:128:| 4b | **A store-catalog app template** | *only* an explicitly fresh, shareable, installable app unrelated to this project's data | `delegate('system-appbuilder','app-architect','build_app',{query})` (`:L253-L263`) |\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/system-spaces/README.md:146:- **Creating a project is a UI action, not a tool.** THING always runs inside an existing project and must not run `build_specialist`/`build_app` to \"make a project\" (`:L82-L88`).\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/system-spaces/README.md:180:For the explicit agreement after THING offers to organize supplied material, this DAG first reads every supplied document and inventories its stable independently-owned scopes; the partition follows the material's primary operational axis (bounded stages in a sequence, independently run operations in parallel), not storage categories such as costs, contacts, documents, or media. It then runs `build_specialist` as a `forEach` over `inventory.scopes` and, once every specialist has finished, delegates the complete source plus attachment IDs to the live-project `automator`. The automator writes the current project's source-derived tables, API, and openable pages, rather than a catalog template; a data model or survey alone is not a completed app. THING invokes this workflow exactly once and consumes its envelope inline with its closing reply: statement-local values cannot safely drive a later continuation, and the returned envelope is the workflow's proof of outcome — THING must not re-inspect the project or validate individual builder results afterwards. Facts, photographs, memories, shared overviews, and cross-cutting groupings stay with their owning scope or app data: they do not become their own specialist. An uninterrupted operational stage can combine its subparts, but separate locations or stages remain separate (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:L457-L484`, `sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/tasklists/organize_material/index.md:L1-L11`, `01-inventory.md:L1-L29`, `02-build_specialist.md:L1-L22`, `03-build_app.md:L1-L24`).\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/system-spaces/README.md:253:### `system-appbuilder/build_app` — `input: { request }`\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/system-spaces/README.md:264:Each fan-out node writes **exactly one file** with the injected authoring globals (`createProject`/`writeTableSchema`/`writeApi`/`writePage`/`writeHook`) (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_app/index.md:L1-L12`, `01-design.md` … `07-finalize.md`).\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/format/project/hooks/event.md:15:- **`handler`** — an imperative async function; the handler IS the filter, with no DSL and no agent/LLM spun up (`sdk/org/libs/cli/src/app/hooks/loader.ts:131-133,138-145`). It is the cheap path for deterministic reactions. A project hook's handler is transpiled and run in-proc (`sdk/org/libs/cli/src/app/hooks/loader.ts:206-244,358-374`); a space hook's handler is run worker-isolated through a shim (`sdk/org/libs/cli/src/app/hooks/loader.ts:271-298,343-356`).\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/cli-api/rest/apps.md:66:2. **Synthesize `project.json` if absent.** Apps authored by `system-appbuilder` ship only a `package.json`; a *deterministic* `{ id, title, description, icon }` is written from the catalog entry (deterministic because `project.json` is part of the install hash — a volatile `createdAt` would make every re-install look diverged) `apps.ts:144-165,236-239`.\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/cli-api/rest/hooks.md:3:Three HTTP routes plus the cron plumbing that drives them. The design principle is stated at the top of the module: **one authoritative run path** — Studio's \"Run now\", the pod's `crond`, the boot catch-up and the in-process fallback tick all funnel through `POST /api/projects/:projectId/hooks/:slug/run` (`sdk/org/libs/cli/src/server/routes/hooks.ts:L2-L20`).\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/app/views.md:109:**Row types** — one `export interface` per `database/<table>.json`, tables sorted for deterministic output `sdk/org/libs/cli/src/app/build/schema.ts:95-120`:\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/app/views.md:148:For views the rule is an **authoring mandate, not an automated gate**. The linter walks only the roots it is handed on argv `sdk/org/libs/css/scripts/lint-design-tokens.mjs:75-90`, and both the root `pnpm lint:tokens` script and the CI job pass the same SPA source trees — `sdk/org/libs/{css,ui}/src`, `sdk/org/apps/web/src`, `com/src social/src team/src store/src space/src blog/src casa/src`, `org/src` — never `store/projects/` or a pod project root `package.json:14`, `.github/workflows/design-tokens.yml:39-43`. (The workflow *triggers* on `store/**`, so touching a shipped project app runs the job — it just never lints that app's pages `.github/workflows/design-tokens.yml:6-27`.) The page build has no color-lint step either `sdk/org/libs/cli/src/app/build/pages.ts`. What actually holds the line for generated apps is the appbuilder prompt: the page-builder agent and the `build_page` tasklist step both mandate tokens only — \"never a raw hex, `rgb()/hsl()`, or a stock Tailwind color\" `sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/agents/page-builder/instruct.md:13-15`, `sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_app/05-build_page.md:12-17`.\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/format/space/agents/frontmatter.md:74:defaultAction: build_app         # runs the build_app action's tasklist host-driven\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/format/space/agents/frontmatter.md:76:  - id: build_app\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/format/space/agents/frontmatter.md:79:    tasklist: build_app          # must resolve in tasklists/\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/format/project/project.json.md:33:Because app-builder-authored apps ship a `package.json` but no `project.json`, the pod's install route synthesizes a **deterministic** `project.json` (`id`/`title`/`description`/`icon` from the catalog entry, no volatile fields) into the installed project directory when one is absent `sdk/org/libs/cli/src/server/routes/apps.ts#ensureProjectJson`. Determinism matters because `project.json` is part of the app-template hash, so a volatile field would make every re-install look diverged `sdk/org/libs/cli/src/server/routes/apps.ts:149-153`.\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/devops/README.md:19:| Load balancer | MetalLB (L2) | `devops/ansible/inventory/test/group_vars/all.yml` |\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/devops/infrastructure.md:178:systemd unit**, *not* MetalLB L2 advertisement — MetalLB is installed and allocates the","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_fzpUJSbHB3H8gLDKEI4xloQi","session_id":"838823e9-9562-4e94-a4a8-ddea09a60dee","uuid":"ddbba825-299b-4d23-bd63-fbcf47773fb0","timestamp":"2026-07-16T06:15:12.120Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace automator structural failure"}
