{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_EKlmzcJsKTt2VMdVuh5YaXqK","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: finalize\n3\toutput:\n4\t  appId: string\n5\t  tables: array\n6\t  pages: array\n7\t  endpoints: array\n8\t  hooks: array\n9\t  ok: boolean\n10\tdependsOn: [create_project, build_table, build_api, build_page, build_hook]\n11\tgoal: true\n12\trole: general\n13\t---\n14\t\n15\tPackage the build result for the caller. This is the GOAL task — it ALWAYS runs and ALWAYS\n16\tresolves a uniform summary of what was built. Upstream arrays arrive by task id: `build_table`\n17\t({ name, ok }[]), `build_api` ({ route, ok }[]), `build_page` ({ route, ok }[]), `build_hook`\n18\t({ slug, ok }[]); `create_project` is { appId, root, ok }. Keep only the pieces that were written\n19\tok. Emit:\n20\t\n21\tconst tables = (Array.isArray(build_table) ? build_table : []).filter((x: { ok: boolean }) => x.ok).map((x: { name: string }) => x.name);\n22\tconst endpoints = (Array.isArray(build_api) ? build_api : []).filter((x: { ok: boolean }) => x.ok).map((x: { route: string }) => x.route);\n23\tconst pages = (Array.isArray(build_page) ? build_page : []).filter((x: { ok: boolean }) => x.ok).map((x: { route: string }) => x.route);\n24\tconst hooks = (Array.isArray(build_hook) ? build_hook : []).filter((x: { ok: boolean }) => x.ok).map((x: { slug: string }) => x.slug);\n25\tcurrentTask.resolve({ appId: create_project.appId, tables, pages, endpoints, hooks, ok: create_project.ok === true });\n26\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"838823e9-9562-4e94-a4a8-ddea09a60dee","uuid":"87aabf6d-4970-4503-ac2d-e202a91ce8f1","timestamp":"2026-07-16T06:16:15.758Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_app/07-finalize.md","content":"---\nid: finalize\noutput:\n  appId: string\n  tables: array\n  pages: array\n  endpoints: array\n  hooks: array\n  ok: boolean\ndependsOn: [create_project, build_table, build_api, build_page, build_hook]\ngoal: true\nrole: general\n---\n\nPackage the build result for the caller. This is the GOAL task — it ALWAYS runs and ALWAYS\nresolves a uniform summary of what was built. Upstream arrays arrive by task id: `build_table`\n({ name, ok }[]), `build_api` ({ route, ok }[]), `build_page` ({ route, ok }[]), `build_hook`\n({ slug, ok }[]); `create_project` is { appId, root, ok }. Keep only the pieces that were written\nok. Emit:\n\nconst tables = (Array.isArray(build_table) ? build_table : []).filter((x: { ok: boolean }) => x.ok).map((x: { name: string }) => x.name);\nconst endpoints = (Array.isArray(build_api) ? build_api : []).filter((x: { ok: boolean }) => x.ok).map((x: { route: string }) => x.route);\nconst pages = (Array.isArray(build_page) ? build_page : []).filter((x: { ok: boolean }) => x.ok).map((x: { route: string }) => x.route);\nconst hooks = (Array.isArray(build_hook) ? build_hook : []).filter((x: { ok: boolean }) => x.ok).map((x: { slug: string }) => x.slug);\ncurrentTask.resolve({ appId: create_project.appId, tables, pages, endpoints, hooks, ok: create_project.ok === true });\n","numLines":26,"startLine":1,"totalLines":26}}}
