{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_aFPx5VeoZN2huCMaP88qaQTv","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: finalize\n3\toutput:\n4\t  appId: string\n5\t  tables: array\n6\t  pages: array\n7\t  endpoints: array\n8\t  hooks: array\n9\t  ok: boolean\n10\tdependsOn: [create_project, build_table, build_api, build_page, build_hook]\n11\tgoal: true\n12\trole: general\n13\t---\n14\t\n15\tPackage the build result for the caller. This is the GOAL task — it ALWAYS runs and ALWAYS\n16\tresolves a uniform summary of what was built. Upstream arrays arrive by task id: `build_table`\n17\t({ name, ok }[]), `build_api` ({ route, ok }[]), `build_page` ({ route, ok }[]), `build_hook`\n18\t({ slug, ok }[]); `create_project` is { appId, root, ok }. Keep only the pieces that were written\n19\tok. Emit:\n20\t\n21\tconst tables = (Array.isArray(build_table) ? build_table : []).filter((x: { ok: boolean }) => x.ok).map((x: { name: string }) => x.name);\n22\tconst endpoints = (Array.isArray(build_api) ? build_api : []).filter((x: { ok: boolean }) => x.ok).map((x: { route: string }) => x.route);\n23\tconst pages = (Array.isArray(build_page) ? build_page : []).filter((x: { ok: boolean }) => x.ok).map((x: { route: string }) => x.route);\n24\tconst hooks = (Array.isArray(build_hook) ? build_hook : []).filter((x: { ok: boolean }) => x.ok).map((x: { slug: string }) => x.slug);\n25\tcurrentTask.resolve({ appId: create_project.appId, tables, pages, endpoints, hooks, ok: create_project.ok === true });\n26\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_fzpUJSbHB3H8gLDKEI4xloQi","session_id":"838823e9-9562-4e94-a4a8-ddea09a60dee","uuid":"492f091d-f9b7-4227-8d3b-dcdac29dc5d6","timestamp":"2026-07-16T06:18:39.078Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace automator structural failure"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_URxnWmxRsIUcHwdYXSHAWd9w","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: design\n3\toutput:\n4\t  appId: string\n5\t  title: string\n6\t  tables: array\n7\t  pages: array\n8\t  endpoints: array\n9\t  hooks: array\n10\tdependsOn: []\n11\trole: general\n12\tfunctions: []\n13\t---\n14\t\n15\tDesign the whole app from `request`. This is the THINKING step: reason from the request into a\n16\tconcrete build plan, then resolve it. You have no file tools here — just produce the plan object.\n17\t\n18\tSubstitute REAL values for every `<…>` below (never leave a placeholder in the resolved values).\n19\tDerive a short lowercase-slug `appId` from the request (letters/digits/hyphen, starts with a\n20\tletter). Each endpoint `route` MUST encode its HTTP method last, e.g. `items-list/GET` or\n21\t`items-create/POST`. Each page `route` is `index` (the app root) or a path like `items/[id]`.\n22\t\n23\tconst appId = \"<lowercase-slug derived from the request, e.g. habit-tracker>\";\n24\tconst title = \"<human-readable app title>\";\n25\t// Each table: { name, schema } where schema = { title, description, columns:{...}, relations? }.\n26\t// Every column and relation needs a description; exactly one primaryKey column (uuid).\n27\tconst tables = [\n28\t  { name: \"<table_slug>\", schema: { title: \"<Title>\", description: \"<what it stores>\", columns: { id: { type: \"string\", description: \"unique id\", primaryKey: true, generated: \"uuid\" } } } }\n29\t];\n30\t// Each endpoint: { route: \"<name>/<METHOD>\", purpose }. Methods: GET|POST|PUT|PATCH|DELETE.\n31\tconst endpoints = [\n32\t  { route: \"<name>/GET\", purpose: \"<what this endpoint returns or does>\" }\n33\t];\n34\t// Each page: { route, purpose }. Use \"index\" for the root page.\n35\tconst pages = [\n36\t  { route: \"index\", purpose: \"<what the root page shows>\" }\n37\t];\n38\t// Each hook (often none): { slug, purpose }. Cron or database-triggered automation.\n39\tconst hooks = [];\n40\tcurrentTask.resolve({ appId, title, tables, pages, endpoints, hooks });\n41\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_fzpUJSbHB3H8gLDKEI4xloQi","session_id":"838823e9-9562-4e94-a4a8-ddea09a60dee","uuid":"22d22763-f4dd-4955-b427-7f4e43af3d37","timestamp":"2026-07-16T06:18:39.079Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace automator structural failure"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_YsZagadFkgbuwYF1FwsSrfid","type":"tool_result","content":"160\t| `system-appbuilder/automator` | `hooks:write`, `db:schema`, `db:read`, `db:write`, `pages:write`, `api:write` | the LIVE-project writers `writeProjectTable`/`Hook`/`Event`/`Api`/`Page` + `db.*` (`system-appbuilder/agents/automator/instruct.md:L7-L13`) |\n161\t| `system-appbuilder/data-modeler` | `db:schema`, `db:read` | `writeTableSchema` (`system-appbuilder/agents/data-modeler/instruct.md:L7-L9`) |\n162\t| `system-appbuilder/page-builder` | `pages:write`, `db:read` | `writePage` (`system-appbuilder/agents/page-builder/instruct.md:L7-L9`) |\n163\t| `system-appbuilder/api-author` | `api:write`, `db:read` | `writeApi` (`system-appbuilder/agents/api-author/instruct.md:L7-L9`) |\n164\t| `system-engineer/engineer` | `fs:scratch` | `createScratch` + a sandboxed generic fs/shell (`readFile`/`writeFile`/`editFile`/`listDir`/`glob`/`grep` + `execShell`, jailed to a throwaway `.lmthing/scratch/<random>` dir) — the engineer's scratch workbench; the ONLY grant that earns any generic filesystem access, and it persists nothing (`sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/capabilities.ts:L93-L97`; `sdk/org/libs/core/src/exec/bootstrap.ts:L146-L167`; `system-engineer/agents/engineer/instruct.md:L12-L13`) |\n165\t| `system-store/finder` | `store:read` | `storeSearch`, `storeInspect` (`sdk/org/libs/core/src/exec/bootstrap.ts:L189-L193`; `system-store/agents/finder/instruct.md:L4-L5`) |\n166\t| `user-thing/thing` | `store:read`, `store:install` | `storeSearch`/`storeInspect` **plus** the consent-marked `installSpace` (`sdk/org/libs/core/src/exec/bootstrap.ts:L195-L198`; `user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:L6-L8`) |\n167\t\n168\t`store:read` survives into read-only fork roles (pure catalog discovery); the mutating `store:install` and `events:emit` are dropped (`sdk/org/libs/core/src/exec/capability.ts:L8-L26`).\n169\t\n170\t> The test's cap-bearing predicate also matches `dir.includes('integration-')` (`sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/capabilities.test.ts:L128`). That clause matches **none** of the ten shipped spaces — it is a leftover from when the `integration-*` spaces (which declare `connections:use`) were bundled; they are store spaces now (`sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/system.test.ts:L60-L62`).\n171\t\n172\t---\n173\t\n174\t## 6. The shipped tasklists (the host-driven DAGs)\n175\t\n176\tSix tasklists ship across four spaces. The tasklist mechanics (`role`, `functions`, `forEach`, `prelude`, `dependsOn`, `goal`, the `{ok, degraded, data}` envelope) are documented in [`../format/space/tasklists/README.md`](../format/space/tasklists/README.md) and [`../runtime/fork-and-tasklists.md`](../runtime/fork-and-tasklists.md) — here is what each shipped DAG actually is.\n177\t\n178\t### `user-thing/organize_material` — `input: { request, sourceSummary, attachmentIds, specialistFacts }`\n179\t\n180\tFor the explicit agreement after THING offers to organize supplied material, this DAG first reads every supplied document and inventories its stable independently-owned scopes; the partition follows the material's primary operational axis (bounded stages in a sequence, independently run operations in parallel), not storage categories such as costs, contacts, documents, or media. It then runs `build_specialist` as a `forEach` over `inventory.scopes` and, once every specialist has finished, delegates the complete source plus attachment IDs to the live-project `automator`. The automator writes the current project's source-derived tables, API, and openable pages, rather than a catalog template; a data model or survey alone is not a completed app. THING invokes this workflow exactly once and consumes its envelope inline with its closing reply: statement-local values cannot safely drive a later continuation, and the returned envelope is the workflow's proof of outcome — THING must not re-inspect the project or validate individual builder results afterwards. Facts, photographs, memories, shared overviews, and cross-cutting groupings stay with their owning scope or app data: they do not become their own specialist. An uninterrupted operational stage can combine its subparts, but separate locations or stages remain separate (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:L457-L484`, `sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/tasklists/organize_material/index.md:L1-L11`, `01-inventory.md:L1-L29`, `02-build_specialist.md:L1-L22`, `03-build_app.md:L1-L24`).\n181\t\n182\t### `user-thing/build_specialist` — `input: { request }`\n183\t\n184\t```\n185\tresearch (explore, optional, prelude-delegates to system-research/researcher#deep_research)\n186\t  → build (goal, general, delegates to system-architect/architect#synthesize_and_run)\n187\t```\n188\t\n189\tThe `research` node is `optional: true` and its **prelude** performs the delegation, so the model's only job is to package the envelope; the `build` node **always runs** (a skipped dependency is satisfied) and returns the built agent's run coordinates `{ spaceKey, agentSlug, actionId, query, ok, errors }` (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/tasklists/build_specialist/index.md:L1-L14`, `01-research.md:L1-L25`, `02-build.md`). The whole research node, verbatim:\n190\t\n191\t````markdown\n192\t---\n193\tid: research\n194\toutput:\n195\t  report: object\n196\tdependsOn: []\n197\toptional: true\n198\tgoal: false\n199\trole: explore\n200\tfunctions: []\n201\tcanDelegateTo:\n202\t  - system-research/researcher#deep_research\n203\tprelude: |\n204\t  const researchEnv = request ? await delegate('system-research', 'researcher', 'deep_research', { query: String(request) }) : { ok: false, degraded: true, data: {} };\n205\t---\n206\t\n207\tPackage the domain research for the build step. …\n208\t\n209\tcurrentTask.resolve({ report: (researchEnv && researchEnv.data) ? researchEnv.data : {} });\n210\t````\n211\t\n212\t### `system-architect/synthesize_and_run` — `input: { topic, goal, research }`\n213\t\n214\t**The shipped DAG is eight nodes** (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/tasklists/synthesize_and_run/01-design.md` … `08-finalize.md`):\n215\t\n216\t```\n217\tdesign (explore, functions: [])\n218\t  → build_field    (forEach: design.fields,    optional, general, [writeKnowledgeIndex, writeKnowledgeOption])\n219\t  → build_function (forEach: design.functions, optional, general, [writeFunctionFile])\n220\t  → write_agent  (general, [writeAgentFile])\n221\t  → write_tasks  (general, [writeTaskFile])\n222\t  → validate     (explore, [validateSpace])\n223\t  → register     (general)\n224\t  → finalize     (goal, explore)\n225\t```\n226\t\n227\tThere is **no research node** — the cited report is handed down in `research` (a JSON *string*) by the caller and seeded straight into `build_field`, so the architect never re-researches (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/tasklists/synthesize_and_run/index.md:L1-L13`; `sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/agents/architect/instruct.md:L36-L63`). Empty/degraded research is **not** a stop condition — the pipeline runs anyway and the built agent carries the knowledge gaps (`:L66-L69`). `finalize` packages `{ spaceKey, agentSlug, actionId, query, ok, errors }`; because `synthesize_and_run` is the action tasklist, its envelope is automatically returned to the caller instead of being manually unpacked in a second model turn.\n228\t\n229\t**Every generated task that loads knowledge carries the grounding rule.** `writeTaskFile` appends it to any instruction containing `loadKnowledge(` that does not already state one (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/functions/writeTaskFile.ts#writeTaskFile`): *state only what the loaded knowledge supports; if it does not answer the query, say so plainly — never infer, guess, or present a conclusion the knowledge does not state.* Without it a fork model asked something its knowledge is **silent** on answers from the nearest note it did load: a built household-insurance agent, asked what its market check concluded, answered from an unrelated car-policy note and told the user a cheaper insurance option had been found — naming their own current insurer — while the saved research row recorded `verified_cheaper_quote_found: false`. The architect's own template writes the rule too (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/tasklists/synthesize_and_run/05-write_tasks.md:L17-L22`); the writer is the backstop that survives the model paraphrasing it.\n230\t\n231\t### `system-architect/iterate_space` — `input: { spaceKey, feedback }`\n232\t\n233\t```\n234\tload (explore) → diagnose (explore) → edit (general) → reregister (general) → redelegate (goal, general)\n235\t```\n236\tLocate the space, diagnose the feedback, re-write only the affected files with the per-file builders, re-validate, re-register, and hand back the re-run parameters (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/tasklists/iterate_space/index.md:L1-L11`).\n237\t\n238\t### `system-research/research` — `input: { query }`\n239\t\n240\tOne node, `answer` (goal, explore, `functions: [webSearch, webFetch]`), whose **prelude** does the whole gather (one `webSearch`, one `webFetch` of the top result) so the model only composes (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-research/tasklists/research/01-answer.md:L1-L16`).\n241\t\n242\t### `system-research/deep_research` — `input: { query }`\n243\t\n244\t```\n245\tscope (explore, [webSearch], prelude: 2 searches)\n246\t  → plan (explore, functions: [])\n247\t  → investigate (forEach: plan.questions, explore, [webSearch, webFetch], prelude: search + fetches)\n248\t  → synthesize (explore, functions: [], prelude: dedup sources + concat findings)\n249\t  → summarize (goal, explore, functions: [])\n250\t```\n251\tEvery deterministic gather/aggregate step lives in a `prelude:`; the model's turns are reserved for synthesis and `resolve` (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-research/tasklists/deep_research/01-scope.md` … `05-summarize.md`). The goal output is the contract THING and the architect destructure: `{ topic, executive_summary, findings[], conclusion, sources[] }`.\n252\t\n253\t### `system-appbuilder/build_app` — `input: { request }`\n254\t\n255\t```\n256\tdesign (general, functions: [])\n257\t  → create_project (general)\n258\t  → build_table (forEach: design.tables,    optional, general)\n259\t  → build_api   (forEach: design.endpoints, general)\n260\t  → build_page  (forEach: design.pages,     general)\n261\t  → build_hook  (forEach: design.hooks,     optional, general)\n262\t  → finalize (goal, general)\n263\t```\n264\tEach fan-out node writes **exactly one file** with the injected authoring globals (`createProject`/`writeTableSchema`/`writeApi`/`writePage`/`writeHook`) (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_app/index.md:L1-L12`, `01-design.md` … `07-finalize.md`).\n265\t\n266\t---\n267\t\n268\t## 7. Materialization onto the pod\n269\t\n270\t### 7.1 `materializeRuntime(root)` — on **every** boot path\n271\t\n272\t`materializeRuntime` copies **every** dir from `defaultSystemSpaceDirs()` into `<root>/system/spaces/<name>/`, records each one's shipped content hash in the manifest, and creates the default `user` project skeleton (`<root>/user/{spaces,documents}/`, an empty `instructions.md`, a `project.json`) (`sdk/org/libs/cli/src/cli/runtime-init.ts#materializeRuntime`). Copying zero spaces is a hard misconfiguration and warns loudly — every session would fail to find the `thing` agent (`:L105-L110`).\n273\t\n274\t`<root>` is `LMTHING_ROOT` when set, else `<cwd>/.lmthing` (`sdk/org/libs/cli/src/cli/bin.ts#resolveLmthingRoot`). On the compute pod it is the data volume (e.g. `LMTHING_ROOT=/data/.lmthing`)."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_fzpUJSbHB3H8gLDKEI4xloQi","session_id":"838823e9-9562-4e94-a4a8-ddea09a60dee","uuid":"1432dd62-505a-435b-abcb-51ec5c162bfb","timestamp":"2026-07-16T06:18:39.080Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace automator structural failure"}
