{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_w9pqX8OtPaFXh3oVw2P3RQDW","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# 06-tanzania — Round 16 report\n2\t\n3\t## Verdict\n4\t\n5\t**Step 2 still fails.** This round fixed and freshly verified the app-build handoff, but the same replay proved that the organizer’s inventory continues to choose cross-cutting facets as specialist scopes rather than the independently owned segments required by the scenario. Per the one-failure rule, the runner was stopped after step 2.\n6\t\n7\t## Change 1 — live-project app handoff\n8\t\n9\t- **Rung:** L2 — a tasklist node selected the wrong existing structural path.\n10\t- **Files:**\n11\t  - `sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/tasklists/organize_material/03-build_app.md`\n12\t  - `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/system-spaces-dag.test.ts`\n13\t  - `org/docs/system-spaces/README.md`\n14\t- **Why this rung:** The first clean replay’s step-2 evidence recorded the node delegating to `system-appbuilder/app-architect/build_app`, then ended with no project tables, no pages, and `built:false`. The full trace shows the catalog action tasklist but no project-writer yields. This is an explicit source-level routing mistake, not a framework failure.\n15\t- **General principle:** A workflow that must change the current project must delegate to the writer whose capabilities target that project. A catalog/template authoring pipeline is not a substitute merely because both are called “app builds.” A data model or survey is not a completed app; the result must expose source-derived rows through project API(s) and page(s).\n16\t- **Before → after:** `03-build_app` formerly allowed and hard-coded `app-architect#build_app`; it now allowlists and calls `automator`, while explicitly requiring source-derived tables/rows plus an openable page backed by the project API. The DAG regression assertion and system-space documentation now name the same live-project path.\n17\t- **Overfit check:** The added prompt and test wording contains no persona, fixture, place, table, or scenario-domain literal. `git diff` grep found no Tanzania-specific term in the changed source/docs/test hunk.\n18\t\n19\t## Evidence\n20\t\n21\t### Failing baseline\n22\t\n23\t`verify-step-02/step-02.json` recorded:\n24\t\n25\t- delegates: three `system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run` plus `system-appbuilder/app-architect/build_app`;\n26\t- state: three spaces, `appTables: {}`, `pageCount: 0`, `built: false`.\n27\t\n28\t`verify-step-02/step-02.full.json:117-127` confirms the organizer’s exact catalog-action delegate and nested catalog tasklists, with no live-project authoring afterwards.\n29\t\n30\t### Verification replay\n31\t\n32\tAfter rebuilding `@lmthing/cli`, `verify-step-02-rerun-2/step-02.json` recorded:\n33\t\n34\t- delegate target changed to `system-appbuilder/automator`;\n35\t- state contains `costs: 9`, `memories: 2`, `stops: 12`, and `tariffs: 4` rows;\n36\t- manifest has four authored pages.\n37\t\n38\t`verify-step-02-rerun-2/step-02.full.json:135-269` confirms the direct automator handoff and later inspection of `_layout.tsx`, `index.tsx`, `costs.tsx`, `memories.tsx`, `tariffs.tsx`, plus four project API route directories. The compact manifest reports `built:false` because the second automator pass cache-hit the page build; page presence is the material result of the corrected handoff.\n39\t\n40\tValidation passed:\n41\t\n42\t```text\n43\tpnpm --dir sdk/org exec vitest run libs/core/src/spaces/system-spaces-dag.test.ts libs/core/src/spaces/prompt-contract.test.ts\n44\t29 passed\n45\t```\n46\t\n47\t(The test loader emitted its pre-existing warning that the automator’s prose mentions `delegate()` despite its empty `canDelegateTo`; this did not fail the suite.)\n48\t\n49\t## Remaining failure — scope partition\n50\t\n51\tThe same fresh verification is still a failure against the first step-2 expectation. It created:\n52\t\n53\t- `Ngorongoro Tariff Reference`\n54\t- `Tanzania Trip Dashboard`\n55\t- `Trip Cost Tracker`\n56\t- `Trip Memories`\n57\t\n58\tThese are cross-cutting facets, exactly the classes `organize_material/01-inventory.md` already prohibits. The expected independently owned segments were not created. The full trace names the four invalid inventory items at `verify-step-02-rerun-2/step-02.full.json:71-108`.\n59\t\n60\tNo web-search/fetch yield appeared, so the supplied-material/no-research behavior held. The app handoff was verified, but the step cannot pass until the partition is reliable.\n61\t\n62\tThe attempt ledger records multiple prior prose adjustments for this decision. Another L1 sentence would repeat an exhausted rung. The next round should design an enforceable, domain-neutral structured partition contract at the `inventory.scopes → build_specialist.forEach` boundary (likely an L3 schema/validation capability if today’s task-output schema cannot express segment ownership, coverage, and forbidden facet classes). It must not restore the catalog handoff, the duplicate direct build path, or a free-form prompt-only partition retry.\n63\t\n64\t## Uncommitted files for review\n65\t\n66\t- `sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/tasklists/organize_material/03-build_app.md`\n67\t- `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/system-spaces-dag.test.ts`\n68\t- `org/docs/system-spaces/README.md`\n69\t- `automation/instances/scenario-campaign/attempts/06-tanzania.md`\n70\t- `automation/instances/scenario-campaign/rounds/16/06-tanzania/PROGRESS.md`\n71\t- `automation/instances/scenario-campaign/rounds/16/06-tanzania/report.md`\n72\t\n73\tNo files were staged or committed.\n74\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_fzpUJSbHB3H8gLDKEI4xloQi","session_id":"838823e9-9562-4e94-a4a8-ddea09a60dee","uuid":"ee0fd6d4-dd9b-4e3b-a2a8-22f2e661ae39","timestamp":"2026-07-16T06:18:48.030Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace automator structural failure"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_hZWjt76VUFAyGqazdHcdFgVr","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Tanzania scenario — round 15 report\n2\t\n3\t## Verdict\n4\t\n5\t**Step 2 failed; not fixed after two fresh verification replays.** Step 1 passed on every replay: all supplied files were read through the document/sheet/vision/audio paths, THING made an offer using real material, and no project state was authored.\n6\t\n7\tThe first replay reproduced the known step-2 failure: `organize_material` executed twice, producing eight overlapping spaces, eleven architect delegates, two appbuilder delegates, and an unbuilt app. The first verification confirmed that the L1 fix removed this re-entry, but exposed a direct-automator completion without any authored project artifacts. The second verification routed app construction through the app architect's action DAG, created exactly four appropriately scoped specialists, and invoked one `app-architect#build_app` delegate; nevertheless the nested build finished before creating a project or authoring a table/page. The app still has `appTables: {}`, `pageCount: 0`, and `built: false`.\n8\t\n9\t## Changes\n10\t\n11\t### L1 — trust a completed workflow envelope\n12\t\n13\t- **File / symbol:** `sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md` — accepted supplied-material offer path.\n14\t- **Test:** `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/prompt-contract.test.ts` — `user-thing supplied-material organization`.\n15\t- **Documentation:** `org/docs/system-spaces/README.md` — `user-thing/organize_material`.\n16\t- **Why this rung:** failing evidence showed two `organize_material` yields in the same user turn. After the first workflow had registered spaces and delegated the app build, THING used `inspect()` to independently rederive project state, encountered a recovered error, and restarted the workflow. The error-prone post-workflow verification was a caller decision, not a missing primitive.\n17\t- **General principle:** once an orchestrating workflow returns its envelope, the caller reports that outcome and stops; it does not independently reconstruct partial results or restart completed work.\n18\t- **Result:** verified. In `verify-step-02/step-02.json`, one organizer yielded one specialist and one direct appbuilder delegate. The original duplicate-work failure was removed.\n19\t\n20\t### L2 — use the deterministic app-build action boundary\n21\t\n22\t- **File / symbol:** `sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/tasklists/organize_material/03-build_app.md`.\n23\t- **Test:** `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/system-spaces-dag.test.ts` — shipped `organize_material` DAG assertions.\n24\t- **Documentation:** `org/docs/system-spaces/README.md` — `user-thing/organize_material`.\n25\t- **Why this rung:** with re-entry gone, the direct `system-appbuilder/automator` delegate returned after a recovered survey-variable typecheck error, but the state contained no tables or pages. A direct broad writer has no deterministic completion boundary. The existing `app-architect#build_app` action owns a host-driven `design → create project → per-file authoring → finalize` tasklist, so selecting that action was the lowest structural correction.\n26\t- **General principle:** a request that must produce a complete multi-step deliverable should go through its fixed action workflow rather than a broad direct writer that can report after an intermediate survey.\n27\t- **Result:** not sufficient. In `verify-step-02-rerun-2/step-02.json`, the runner recorded exactly four specialist-space delegates and one `system-appbuilder/app-architect/build_app` delegate. Its full evidence records nested `build_app` tasklist yields, but no `createProject`, table, API, or page writer yields. The final project has no app artifacts.\n28\t\n29\t## Evidence\n30\t\n31\t### Initial failure\n32\t\n33\t`attempt-1/step-02.json`:\n34\t\n35\t- eleven architect delegates and two automator delegates;\n36\t- `spaceCount: 8` with overlapping names including `Cairo Stopover`, `Northern Tanzania Safari`, `Tanzania Safari Tracker`, and duplicate Zanzibar/Arusha variants;\n37\t- populated source rows but `appManifest.built: false`.\n38\t\n39\t`attempt-1/step-02.full.json` records the first `organize_material` yield at lines 43–46 and a second at lines 233–236. Between them, the first run had already registered spaces and delegated the app builder.\n40\t\n41\t### First verification — L1 works, direct writer does not\n42\t\n43\t`verify-step-02/step-02.json`:\n44\t\n45\t- one architect delegate and one `system-appbuilder/automator` delegate;\n46\t- `spaceCount: 1`, but `appTables: {}` and `built: false`.\n47\t\n48\t`verify-step-02/step-02.full.json:138-142` records the direct automator's recovered `Cannot find name 'existingTables'`, `existingPages`, `existingHooks`, and `existingEvents` error while it attempted to return a survey result. No project mutation followed.\n49\t\n50\t### Final verification — L2 action handoff still returns early\n51\t\n52\t`verify-step-02-rerun-2/step-02.json`:\n53\t\n54\t- four architect delegates, one `system-appbuilder/app-architect/build_app` delegate, and no duplicate organizer invocation;\n55\t- four scopes: `Itinerary Logistics`, `Ngorongoro Crater Safari`, `Trip Costs & Budget`, and `Zanzibar & Stone Town`;\n56\t- no web-search/fetch yields;\n57\t- `appTables: {}`, `pageCount: 0`, `built: false`.\n58\t\n59\t`verify-step-02-rerun-2/step-02.full.json:124-134` records the action delegate and its two nested `build_app` tasklist yields. There are no `createProject`, `writeTableSchema`, `writeApi`, or `writePage` yields anywhere in the trace. The remaining issue is therefore inside the nested action-tasklist handoff or completion path, not supplied-material routing, scope inventory, or the direct-writer choice.\n60\t\n61\t## Validation\n62\t\n63\t- `pnpm --dir sdk/org --filter @lmthing/core test -- src/spaces/prompt-contract.test.ts src/spaces/system-spaces-dag.test.ts` — passed.\n64\t- `pnpm --dir sdk/org --filter @lmthing/cli... build` — passed after each source update.\n65\t- `pnpm docs:check` — passed: 118 documents, 4,556 citations.\n66\t- Prompt-diff literal check found no new scenario-specific terms in `organize_material`; existing Tanzania/Cairo examples elsewhere pre-date this round and were not modified.\n67\t- `git diff --check` — passed.\n68\t\n69\t## Remaining failure / next attribution\n70\t\n71\tDo not restore THING's direct app-building path or the direct automator delegation: both were independently proved unsound. The next invocation should trace why an explicit `app-architect#build_app` action emits an outer tasklist yield and then a completed inner `build_app` yield without executing its declared `design`, `create_project`, per-file, and `finalize` nodes. Start at `sdk/org/libs/core/src/delegate/delegate.ts#runDelegate`, `sdk/org/libs/core/src/eval/yield-router.ts#routeCommonYield`, and `sdk/org/libs/core/src/tasklist/orchestrator.ts#runTasklist`, comparing the action delegate's tasklist envelope/capture behavior with a top-level app-architect invocation. This is now a candidate framework completion/handoff gap, but no L3 change was made because this round did not yet prove which lower-level handoff is missing.\n72\t\n73\tAll changes remain uncommitted for human review.\n74\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_fzpUJSbHB3H8gLDKEI4xloQi","session_id":"838823e9-9562-4e94-a4a8-ddea09a60dee","uuid":"3072ab4f-e74e-4216-ba0b-4f37f5bec3df","timestamp":"2026-07-16T06:18:48.031Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace automator structural failure"}
