{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_ZktYfufrmnYw4IBGhvOTcnQL","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Capability model\n2\t\n3\tThe authoring globals are not ambient — each is host-injected ONLY for an agent that holds the\n4\tmatching `capabilities:` grant in its `instruct.md` frontmatter. A grant that is absent is absent\n5\tfrom both the injected globals AND the typecheck DTS, so a stray call fails typecheck instead of\n6\treaching the engine. This is least-privilege: give an agent exactly the caps its job needs.\n7\t\n8\t## The grants and what they unlock\n9\t\n10\t| Capability | Unlocks | Config |\n11\t|---|---|---|\n12\t| `project:manage` | `createProject`, `selectProject` | bare (no config) |\n13\t| `db:schema` | `writeTableSchema`, `db.createTable`/`db.addColumn` | optional `{ tables: [...] }` |\n14\t| `db:read` | `db.query`, `db.tables` | optional `{ tables: [...] }` |\n15\t| `db:write` | `db.insert`, `db.update`, `db.remove` | optional `{ tables: [...] }` |\n16\t| `pages:write` | `writePage`, `writeProjectPage` | bare |\n17\t| `api:write` | `writeApi`, `writeProjectApi` | bare |\n18\t| `hooks:write` | `writeHook` | bare |\n19\t| `api:call` | `apiCall(name, input)` | required `{ allow: [...] }` |\n20\t| `connections:use` | `callConnection`, `integrationStatus` | optional `{ providers: [...] }` |\n21\t| `store:read` | `storeSearch`, `storeInspect` | bare |\n22\t| `store:install` | `installSpace` (consent-gated) | bare |\n23\t| `events:emit` | `emitEvent` | bare |\n24\t| `fs:scratch` | scratch-dir file access | bare |\n25\t\n26\tThat is the complete set of recognized ids — 13 in all; an unknown id fails the space load.\n27\t\n28\t## Declaring capabilities\n29\t\n30\t`capabilities:` is a YAML list. An entry is either a bare id or a single-key map carrying config:\n31\t\n32\t```yaml\n33\tcapabilities:\n34\t  - project:manage          # bare\n35\t  - db:schema               # bare = all tables\n36\t  - db:read: { tables: [items, comments] }   # narrowed to named tables\n37\t  - pages:write\n38\t  - api:write\n39\t  - hooks:write\n40\t```\n41\t\n42\t- `db:read`/`db:write`/`db:schema` accept an optional `{ tables: [...] }` that narrows the grant to\n43\t  named tables; bare = all tables. The `db` object exposes only the verbs of the granted db caps.\n44\t- `pages:write`/`api:write`/`hooks:write`/`project:manage` are BARE — passing a config is an error.\n45\t- `api:call` REQUIRES a non-empty `{ allow: [...] }` allowlist (there is no \"call anything\").\n46\t- An unknown capability id fails the space load (fail-loud).\n47\t\n48\t## Least-privilege in practice\n49\t\n50\tThe `app-architect` orchestrator holds the full authoring set (it builds every file kind). The\n51\tspecialist agents hold only their slice: `data-modeler` = `db:schema`+`db:read`; `page-builder` =\n52\t`pages:write`+`db:read`; `api-author` = `api:write`+`db:read`. The `automator` is the broad one — it\n53\tauthors the LIVE project (data model + automation + UI) and so holds six grants:\n54\t`hooks:write`, `db:schema`, `db:read`, `db:write`, `pages:write`, `api:write`. A page\n55\tbuilder cannot write a table; a data modeler cannot write a page. The build_app tasklist runs its\n56\tper-file steps with role `general` under the app-architect's own grants, so every write global is\n57\tcallable in those task bodies without any extra delegation.\n58\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_fzpUJSbHB3H8gLDKEI4xloQi","session_id":"838823e9-9562-4e94-a4a8-ddea09a60dee","uuid":"85505704-59c1-44a1-ba8c-147533722124","timestamp":"2026-07-16T06:18:48.157Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace automator structural failure"}
