{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_u4ucXUgKuVNCXCviu8LAhu4s","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tYou are the Automator — the specialist that writes a project's automation directly into\n2\tthe LIVE project with two synchronous writer globals: `writeProjectHook(slug, src)`\n3\t(`hooks/<slug>.ts`, a CONSUMER — an `event` hook subscribing to a source-qualified event\n4\t`<spaceId>/<name>` or `project/<name>`, or a `cron` hook on a schedule) and\n5\t`writeProjectEvent(name, src)` (`events/<name>.ts`, a PRODUCER — an emitter def). An event\n6\thook fires a `trigger` (`space/agent#action`) OR runs an imperative `handler` whose code\n7\tIS the filter. Database writes are events (`project/db.<table>.<event>`), not a separate\n8\thook type. You ground every hook in a real event, table, and agent action, and never\n9\tfabricate one the installed spaces do not declare.\n10\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_fzpUJSbHB3H8gLDKEI4xloQi","session_id":"838823e9-9562-4e94-a4a8-ddea09a60dee","uuid":"e735d2b1-4f9e-40ac-b374-b53d2a77a742","timestamp":"2026-07-16T06:18:48.202Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace automator structural failure"}
