{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_04dKYLQahIrlclNDzAzCpxkm","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: inventory\n3\toutput:\n4\t  scopes: array\n5\trole: explore\n6\tfunctions: []\n7\tprelude: |\n8\t  const documents = await Promise.all((attachmentIds as string[]).map((id) => readDocument(id)));\n9\t---\n10\t\n11\tIdentify the coarsest complete partition of independently owned scopes in the supplied material.\n12\t`request`, `sourceSummary`, `attachmentIds`, and `specialistFacts` are in scope. The host has already\n13\tread every supplied document into `documents`; source text is authoritative over the short summary.\n14\tUse the material's primary operational axis: when it describes a sequence, partition it into its\n15\tbounded stages; when it describes parallel operations, partition it by the independently run operation.\n16\tA scope has an objective, its own body of facts, and a later-answer boundary; do not merge it into a\n17\tbroad overview because it has few facts. Each supplied fact belongs to one scope only: never emit a\n18\tchild scope when its questions and facts can be answered by its parent. A scope is a stable operational\n19\tpart of the user's material, NOT an individual expense, note, reminder, fact, photo, memory, person,\n20\tbooking, record type, shared overview, or cross-cutting grouping. Costs, contacts, documents, media,\n21\tand records are facets of the owning scope or app data, never their own scope. Combine adjacent subparts\n22\twhen they serve one continuous purpose; otherwise give each independently owned operation its own scope.\n23\tBefore resolving, reject any candidate whose topic names a format, record category, or supporting facet\n24\trather than a bounded operational stage or independently run operation. Include every stable scope\n25\trepresented in the source, but do not split one merely because it has several kinds of details.\n26\t\n27\tFor each scope, emit `{ topic, goal, research }`, where `research` is a JSON-stringifiable object\n28\twith `topic`, `executive_summary`, `findings`, `conclusion`, and `sources`. Ground its findings only\n29\tin the supplied document text and `specialistFacts`; sources must be empty because supplied material\n30\tis not web research. Emit ONE `currentTask.resolve({ scopes: [...] })` statement."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_fzpUJSbHB3H8gLDKEI4xloQi","session_id":"838823e9-9562-4e94-a4a8-ddea09a60dee","uuid":"1933e2e1-d179-4768-a8f9-ded57f020c0d","timestamp":"2026-07-16T06:19:13.034Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace automator structural failure"}
