{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_HgXOL73AMOcxWMUurNBRfQu0","type":"tool_result","content":"     1\t---\n     2\tid: read_sources\n     3\toutput:\n     4\t  summary: string\n     5\t  ok: boolean\n     6\tdependsOn: []\n     7\trole: explore\n     8\tfunctions: []\n     9\tprelude: |\n    10\t  const documents = await Promise.all((attachmentIds as string[]).map((id) => readDocument(id)));\n    11\t---\n    12\t\n    13\tRead every supplied document before building. `query`, `attachmentIds`, and `documents` are in\n    14\tscope. Extract the concrete records and values the user supplied, including values in sheets and PDFs;\n    15\timage/audio facts already included in `request` remain source facts too. Produce a compact, complete\n    16\tplain-text build brief that names the records, values, dates, references, and contacts that must reach\n    17\tthe live project. Do not research the web. Emit exactly one statement:\n    18\t\n    19\t```typescript\n    20\tcurrentTask.resolve({ summary: '<complete source-derived build brief>', ok: true });\n    21\t```\n     1\t---\n     2\tid: write_data\n     3\toutput:\n     4\t  tables: array\n     5\t  rows: number\n     6\t  ok: boolean\n     7\tdependsOn: [read_sources]\n     8\trole: general\n     9\tfunctions: []\n    10\t---\n    11\t\n    12\tWrite the complete source-derived data model into the LIVE project. `query` and `read_sources` are\n    13\tin scope. Use `writeProjectTable(name, schema, rows)` for every table so each matching source record\n    14\tlands as a row at creation; never create an empty table when the source has matching data. Include the\n    15\tsource's identifiers, contacts, dates, payments, stated totals, and attribution. This is a bounded\n    16\twrite node: do not write pages or APIs here and do not rely on a value declared by an earlier model\n    17\tstatement. Emit exactly one self-contained statement that performs all table writes and resolves the\n