{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_FFJKMOVjsfKJlWJZsycaWrdj","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Confirmed defects:\n\n1. **Data-write failure does not block the completion node** — `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/03-write_openable_app.md:7`  \n   `dependsOn: [write_data]` waits only for `write_data` to resolve; it does not require `write_data.ok === true`. If a `writeProjectTable` fails, `write_data` can resolve `{ ok: false }`, then `write_openable_app` still writes parse-valid API/page source and resolves success. The tasklist can therefore report a completed openable app whose tables/seed rows were never created.\n\n2. **Caller treats task-execution success as application success** — `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/tasklists/organize_material/03-build_app.md:24`  \n   The delegate result is a `TaskEnvelope`; `app.ok` means the goal fork resolved without degradation, not that `app.data.ok` is true. If the completion node correctly reports `{ ok: false }` because its API/page writes failed, this expression still resolves the outer goal as `{ ok: true }`, falsely marking the app build successful.\n\n3. **The new action instruction contradicts delegate action dispatch and permits result replacement** — `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/agents/automator/instruct.md:48`  \n   A bare `await tasklist(...)` does not return directly from `runDelegate`; the yield resumes the delegate’s turn loop for another model turn. The runtime auto-captures the tasklist envelope, but a subsequent `currentTask.resolve(...)` overwrites that captured value. This conflicts with the action-dispatch hint in `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/src/delegate/delegate.ts:225-229`, which requires binding and resolving the result, and makes the claimed single-statem