{"type":"system","subtype":"commands_changed","commands":[{"name":"claude-hud:setup","description":"(claude-hud) Configure claude-hud as your statusline","argumentHint":""},{"name":"claude-hud:configure","description":"(claude-hud) Configure HUD display options (layout, language, presets, display elements) while preserving advanced manual overrides","argumentHint":""},{"name":"howl:configure","description":"(howl) Configure Howl statusline display preset with interactive guidance and preview","argumentHint":""},{"name":"howl:customize","description":"(howl) Customize Howl statusline with fine-grained metric toggles and priority ordering","argumentHint":""},{"name":"howl:setup","description":"(howl) This skill should be used when the user asks to \"install howl\", \"set up the statusline\", \"configure howl\", \"enable the HUD\", or \"install the statusline binary\". It downloads the Howl binary and configures Claude Code to use it.","argumentHint":""},{"name":"howl:threshold","description":"(howl) Customize Howl color thresholds and behavior triggers interactively","argumentHint":""},{"name":"design-sync","description":"Push a React design system to claude.ai/design. This runs a converter that bundles the real component code (from Storybook or a bare package) and uploads it. Use when the user runs /design-sync or says \"sync my design system to Claude Design\".","argumentHint":"[<project hint, e.g. \"Acme DS\">]"},{"name":"dataviz","description":"Use this skill whenever you are about to create ANY chart, graph, plot, dashboard, or data visualization, in ANY output medium — an HTML or React artifact, inline SVG, plotting code in any library (matplotlib, plotly, d3, Recharts, …), an image/PNG you will render and upload, or a chart shared into Slack. Read it BEFORE writing the first line of chart code, choosing chart colors, building a stat tile / meter / KPI row, or laying out a dashboard. Produces visualizations that read as one system — elegant, accessible, consiste