{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_XmrQ6T85gsx3NBHFfSaUqV24","type":"tool_result","content":"sdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/cairo-stopover-advisor/functions/buildItinerary.ts\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/cairo-stopover-advisor/functions/scoreSight.ts\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/stone-town-advisor/functions/scoreSite.ts\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-camping/knowledge/crater-day/what-to-expect/index.md:6:What to expect on Ngorongoro Crater day: your driver-guide (Emmanuel, not Richard from the office), the ranger tip of approximately 5,000 TZS in cash expected at the gate separate from official park fees, and the presence of Maasai craft vendors at the crater site where beaded items can be purchased. Richard remains the Suricata office contact for clarifying any fee questions before final payment.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-camping/knowledge/logistics/pre-safari/index.md:6:Pre-safari logistics cover the Arusha accommodation and the Suricata Safaris office contact arrangements. The trip includes a 2-night pre-safari stay at Serengeti Villa in Arusha (Aug 5–7, 2026), providing a base before departing for the 3-day group camping safari on the northern circuit. The Suricata Safaris office point of contact is Richard, who handles questions and payment confirmations; the driver-guide on crater day will be Emmanuel, a separate team member. Travelers should confirm any fee questions (such as the ranger tip) with Richard before settling the safari balance.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-camping/knowledge/crater-day/what-to-expect/ranger-tips.md:3:At the Ngorongoro Conservation Area gate, the driver-guide Emmanuel mentioned that a ranger tip of approximately 5,000 TZS is expected in cash at the gate. This tip is separate from the official park entry fees set by the Ngorongoro Conservation Area Authority (NCAA). It is payable directly in Tanzanian shillings, so having small-denomination cash on hand is advisable. The user intends to confirm the exact amount and expectation with Richard (the Suricata Safaris office contact) before paying the safari balance.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-camping/knowledge/crater-day/what-to-expect/guide-info.md:3:On crater day, the driver-guide is Emmanuel — not Richard, who is based at the Suricata Safaris office in Arusha. Emmanuel is the field guide who accompanies the group into Ngorongoro Crater and provides on-the-ground information about park rules, wildlife, and logistics including the ranger tip expectation. Richard remains the primary office contact for pre-safari questions, fee clarifications, and balance payments. The distinction matters: Emmanuel is your guide inside the parks, while Richard handles bookings and administrative queries from the office.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-camping/knowledge/logistics/pre-safari/suricata-office-contact.md:3:The primary office contact for Suricata Safaris is **Richard**, who handles inquiries, booking confirmations, and payment matters. Note that Richard is the office-based contact — he is **not** the driver-guide on the safari. The crater-day driver-guide is **Emmanuel**, a different team member. If you have questions about park fees, the ranger tip (~5,000 TZS in cash at the Ngorongoro gate), or any other safari details, Richard is the person to confirm with before paying the final safari balance.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ddf06e51-7358-4abc-8049-dd6b1803b5d8","u