its own actions/tasklists). */\n30\t  action?: string;\n31\t  /** Subset of action ids the calling agent's `canDelegateTo` permits on this target.\n32\t   *  `undefined` = unrestricted (all actions, including the no-action model-driven\n33\t   *  form, are allowed) — e.g. the session's top-level entry point, which has no\n34\t   *  delegator-side restriction to enforce. Populated by the yield-router/session\n35\t   *  layer from the delegator's resolved `ResolvedDep.allowedActions`. */\n36\t  allowedActions?: string[];\n37\t  delegateOpts?: DelegateOpts;\n38\t  registry: DelegateRegistry;\n39\t  renderHost: RenderHost;\n40\t  streamFn: (opts: StreamOpts) => Promise<StreamSession>;\n41\t  depth: number;\n42\t  maxDepth: number;\n43\t  maxConcurrentForks: number;\n44\t  clock?: Clock;\n45\t  tracer?: Tracer;\n46\t  /** Parent execution scope for hierarchical observability. */\n47\t  scope?: TraceScope;\n48\t  systemSpaces?: Space[];\n49\t  /** Absolute path to the project's spaces/ dir. Propagated into the delegate VM as\n50\t   *  LMTHING_PROJECT_SPACES_DIR and forwarded to nested delegate/fork VMs. */\n51\t  projectSpacesDir?: string;\n52\t  /** Absolute project root — the delegated specialist operates on the PARENT's project\n53\t   *  (LMTHING_PROJECT_DIR), so app grants resolve against the current project, not the\n54\t   *  system space the specialist lives in. Forwarded to nested delegates/forks. */\n55\t  projectRoot?: string;\n56\t  /** Project id — forwarded as LMTHING_PROJECT_ID. */\n57\t  projectId?: string;\n58\t  /** Host-provided app-global engine impls (libs/cli, P2+), forwarded to the delegate\n59\t   *  VM and its nested forks so a delegated db-writer reaches the project's engine. */\n60\t  appGlobals?: AppGlobalImpls;\n61\t  /** Host resolver for the universal `readDocument` global — threaded from the session\n62\t   *  (project-independent, NOT an app-global) so a delegated files agent can read an\n63\t   *  attached upload's text. Forwarded verbatim to nested delegates + forks. */\n64\t  documentResolver?: DocumentResolver;\n65\t  /** Model spec/alias used by streamFn — forwarded to runTurnLoop so llm_request events\n66\t   *  carry a model field and cost tracking works across delegate chains. Overridden\n67\t   *  by the delegated agent's own `model:` frontmatter when set (e.g. a vision agent). */\n68\t  model?: string;\n69\t  /** Multimodal attachments (image/binary-file MediaParts) to attach to the\n70\t   *  delegated agent's initial user message — lets THING route an image to a\n71\t   *  vision agent. Resolved by the session's runDelegate from `attachmentIds`. */\n72\t  attachments?: MediaPart[];\n73\t  /** Id-anchored notes for file attachments, appended to the delegated agent's\n74\t   *  message telling it to fetch each file's content via `readDocument(id)`. */\n75\t  attachmentTexts?: string[];\n76\t  /** Host budget caps inherited from the parent context (session opts, or the outer\n77\t   *  delegate layer). Applied to each fork THIS delegate spawns (fresh Budget per\n78\t   *  fork) — not to the delegate's own turn loop. Before the A1 fix this was\n79\t   *  silently dropped at the delegate boundary, so leaf forks nested under a\n80\t   *  delegate ran uncapped and never received the near-limit \"resolve NOW\" nudge. */\n81\t  budgetLimits?: BudgetLimits;\n82\t  /** Per-role fork model assignment inherited from the parent session (A1 fix —\n83\t   *  previously dropped, so explore/plan forks under a delegate ran on the wrong model). */\n84\t  roleModels?: RoleModelConfig;\n85\t  /** Spaces registered at runtime via registerSpace() — the SAME Map reference the\n86\t   *  parent Session owns, so a registerSpace() inside a fork under this delegate is\n87\t   *  visible to later parent delegate() calls (A1 fix — previously a dead path). */\n88\t  dynamicSpaces?: Map<string, Space>;\n89\t}\n90\t\n91\texport async function runDelegate(opts: RunDelegateOpts): Promise<unknown> {\n92\t  const target = `${opts.packageName}/${opts.agentName}`;\n93\t\n94\t  if (opts.depth >= opts.maxDepth) {\n95\t    throw new Error(\n96\t      `Maximum delegation depth (${opts.maxDepth}) exceeded at target \"${target}\"`,\n97\t    );\n98\t  }\n99\t\n100\t  const { space, agent } = await opts.registry.resolveLazy(target);\n101\t\n102\t  // The delegated agent may declare its own model (frontmatter `model:`), e.g. a\n103\t  // vision agent needing a vision-capable model. Its own turns run on that model;\n104\t  // fall back to the caller's inherited model when unset.\n105\t  const turnModel = agent.model ?? opts.model;\n106\t\n107\t  // Seed registry with this space's npm deps so nested delegates can resolve them\n108\t  for (const [pkgName, depSpace] of Object.entries(space.dependentSpaces)) {\n109\t    opts.registry.addSpace(pkgName, depSpace);\n110\t    opts.registry.addSpace(depSpace.dir, depSpace);\n111\t  }\n112\t\n113\t  // Enforce the delegator's canDelegateTo action restriction, when known. The caller\n114\t  // (globals/delegate.ts's yield handler, via the yield-router) passes the resolved\n115\t  // dependency's `allowedActions` for the target agent; `undefined` means \"not\n116\t  // restricted at the caller layer\" (e.g. the top-level session entry point, or a\n117\t  // dependency-less call) and `[]`/populated arrays gate which actions may run.\n118\t  if (opts.action && opts.allowedActions && !opts.allowedActions.includes(opts.action)) {\n119\t    throw new Error(\n120\t      `Delegate target \"${target}\" does not allow action \"${opts.action}\" — allowed actions: ${opts.allowedActions.length ? opts.allowedActions.join(', ') : '(none)'}`,\n121\t    );\n122\t  }\n123\t\n124\t  const tracer = opts.tracer ?? NULL_TRACER;\n125\t  const delegateLabel = `delegate:${opts.packageName}/${opts.agentName}/${opts.action ?? '(model-driven)'}`;\n126\t  // Mint a delegate scope for full observability; end() in finally below\n127\t  const queryPreview =\n128\t    typeof opts.delegateOpts?.query === 'string'\n129\t      ? opts.delegateOpts.query.slice(0, 500)\n130\t      : undefined;\n131\t  const delegateScope = tracer.child(opts.scope, 'delegate', delegateLabel, {\n132\t    pkg: opts.packageName,\n133\t    agent: opts.agentName,\n134\t    action: opts.action,\n135\t    depth: opts.depth,\n136\t    ...(queryPreview !== undefined ? { query: queryPreview } : {}),\n137\t  });\n138\t\n139\t  // Unified canDelegateTo semantics: the DELEGATED agent's own policy decides\n140\t  // whether `delegate` exists in its VM/DTS/prompt, and (yield-time, below)\n141\t  // which targets its calls may hit. Omitted = unrestricted (back-compat);\n142\t  // [] = none; [\"*\"] = unrestricted; list = hard allowlist (+ \"registered:*\").\n143\t  const delegatePolicy = evaluateDelegatePolicy(agent.canDelegateTo, 'agent');\n144\t  const directDeps = resolveDirectDeps(space, agent.canDelegateTo);\n145\t\n146\t  // The universal `global` toolkit (readFile, grep, remember, …) is injected into every\n147\t  // delegate VM below. Surface it in the system prompt AND the typecheck overlay too —\n148\t  // otherwise an agent that calls a bare global tool (e.g. the memory agent's remember())\n149\t  // fails typecheck with \"Cannot find name\", since it declares no functions of its own.\n150\t  const systemFnSources = systemFunctionSources(opts.systemSpaces ?? []);\n151\t  const knowledgePreloads = await resolvePreloadedKnowledge(space, agent);\n152\t  const systemBlock = buildSystemBlock({ space, agent, directDeps, systemFunctions: systemFnSources, knowledgePreloads, omitAsk: true, omitDelegate: delegatePolicy.mode === 'none' });\n153\t\n154\t  // The delegated agent runs with ITS OWN declared app grants, but project-rooted at\n155\t  // the PARENT's projectRoot (forwarded below) — so a delegated specialist mutates the\n156\t  // current project's app, not the system space it lives in.\n157\t  const capabilities = delegateCapabilities(delegatePolicy.mode !== 'none', agent.capabilities ?? {});\n158\t\n159\t  // action is optional. When provided it must exist; when omitted the agent runs\n160\t  // model-driven and may initiate one of its own actions' tasklists (its # Actions\n161\t  // section is rendered into the system prompt by buildSystemBlock).\n162\t  const actionDef = opts.action ? agent.actions.find((a) => a.id === opts.action) : undefined;\n163\t  if (opts.action && !actionDef) {\n164\t    throw new Error(`Action \"${opts.action}\" not found on agent \"${agent.slug}\"`);\n165\t  }\n166\t\n167\t  const query = opts.delegateOpts?.query ?? '';\n168\t  const context = opts.delegateOpts?.context;\n169\t\n170\t  // Result capture. Tasklists whose result should be auto-captured if the model"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ddf06e51-7358-4abc-8049-dd6b1803b5d8","uuid":"a9fc5c59-7b9c-4ace-8649-7e10c074ec3c","timestamp":"2026-07-16T06:49:56.147Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/src/delegate/delegate.ts","content":"import type { RenderHost, Clock } from '../session/types.js';\nimport type { StreamOpts, StreamSession, MediaPart } from '../eval/stream-types.js';\nimport type { DelegateOpts } from '../globals/delegate.js';\nimport type { DelegateRegistry } from './registry.js';\nimport type { Tracer, TraceScope } from '../sandbox/trace.js';\nimport { NULL_TRACER } from '../sandbox/trace.js';\nimport { resolveDirectDeps, getAgentFunctions, getAgentFunctionsBundled } from '../spaces/agent.js';\nimport { getAgentComponents } from '../spaces/components.js';\nimport { MessageHistory } from '../context/history.js';\nimport { buildSystemBlock, resolvePreloadedKnowledge } from '../context/system-block.js';\nimport { runTurnLoop } from '../eval/turn-loop.js';\nimport { routeCommonYield } from '../eval/yield-router.js';\nimport { buildOverlay } from '../typecheck/overlay.js';\nimport { systemFunctionSources, systemFunctionsBundled } from '../spaces/system.js';\nimport type { Spa