ite stucco walls, arched windows, dark carved wooden balconies, ornate Middle Eastern/Mediterranean feel, no people, no readable signs\\n- Attach as a memory/photo note in the Zanzibar section\\n\\n=== SPECIALIST SPACES BUILT ===\\n1. \\\"Tanzania Safari — Northern Circuit (Ngorongoro, Serengeti, Manyara)\\\" — covers safari itinerary, costs, park fees, voice note details\\n2. \\\"Stone Town, Zanzibar\\\" — covers Zanzibar leg, courtyard photo, accommodation\\n3. \\\"Cairo Stopover\\\" — covers Cairo transit/layover portion\\n\\n=== DATABASE TABLES TO SEED ===\\n1. trips: id, title (\\\"Tanzania Safari & Zanzibar 2026\\\"), start_date (2026-08-03), end_date (2026-08-20), status (\\\"booked\\\")\\n2. trip_segments: trip_id, segment (Cairo, Safari, Zanzibar), dates, notes\\n3. expenses: trip_id, description, category, amount, currency (USD/TZS), payment_status, date, notes\\n   - All rows from trip-costs.xlsx\\n   - Bracelet purchase: \\\"$20-25\\\", ~35,000 TZS, category \\\"souvenirs\\\", notes \\\"2 beaded bracelets from Maasai lady, Ngorongoro crater day\\\"\\n   - Ranger tip: ~5,000 TZS, category \\\"tips\\\", status \\\"pending confirmation\\\", notes \\\"Emmanuel mentioned extra ranger tip at gate — ask Richard before safari balance payment\\\"\\n4. park_fees: park (\\\"Ngorongoro Conservation Area\\\"), fee_type, amount, currency, per (person/day/vehicle), notes\\n   - All rows from ngorongoro-conservation-area-tariffs.pdf\\n5. contacts: name, role, organization, notes\\n   - Richard: Suricata Safaris, office contact, balance/tip questions\\n   - Emmanuel: driver/guide, Ngorongoro crater day\\n6. memories: trip_id, type (\\\"photo\\\"), title (\\\"Stone Town courtyard\\\"), location (\\\"Stone Town, Zanzibar\\\"), description (architectural details per image analysis), attachment_ref (\\\"stone-town-zanzibar.jpg\\\")\\n\\n=== PAGES/VIEWS TO BUILD ===\\n- Trip overview page: itinerary timeline, segments, key contacts\\n- Expenses page: table with filters by cat